com.slightlyloony.blog.objects

Class BlogObjectMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.slightlyloony.blog.objects.BlogObject
      • com.slightlyloony.blog.objects.BlogObjectObject
        • com.slightlyloony.blog.objects.BlogObjectMetadata

  • public class BlogObjectMetadata
extends BlogObjectObject
    Contains all the information needed for the blog server to be able to produce a response to a request, other than the actual content. This information is persisted in the blog storage system as JSON files (file extension ".meta"), and methods are included to encode and decode objects of this class. There is a custom serializer in order to provide one particular little bit of magic: fields with default values are completely left out, in order to minimize the size of the on-disk object. This is less for saving space (as each file will be 4k minimum anyway), and more about minimizing the deserialization time.
    Author:
    Tom Dilatush tom@dilatush.com
